Taranaki gate
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a makeshift gate of wire and battens, difficult to open and shut.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: Irishman's gate; ten-minute gate
Pronunciation:
Notes: Irishman's gate; ten-minute gate		aka taranaki, Taranaki as abbreviations
